						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in a field about 1 km to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśiva.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the royal grant of land in the village Mogiḷakālava, probably a hamlet of Kalūru <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śrīraṅgarāja-samudram to Tirumala-Narahari-Tātāchāryuluṁgāru. The gift is stated to have been made on the banks of the Tuṅgabhadra and in the presence of god Viṭhalēśvara.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of Andhra Pradesh;</hi> Cuddapah District, Part II, No. 269.]</p>						

						</summary>
